The Madoff scandal has ensnared wealthy Americans and retirees, leaving many destitute.
Clients discovered Madoff's empty coffers when trying to withdraw funds, revealing a global fraud scheme.
The veteran Wall Street figure confessed to a $50 billion Ponzi scheme, shocking investors.
European banks suffered losses, with Spain's Santander potentially losing billions.
The regulatory system's failure is under scrutiny, as investors unknowingly poured money into the fraudulent funds.
The impact is compared to the Lehman Brothers collapse.
